author: National Geographic
description:
Internal Investigation
CBP Miami investigates a traveler suspected of smuggling drugs internally. In New York, HSI conducts a controlled delivery of ecstasy on Wall Street. 

Cocaine Crackdown
HSI MIA conducts a sting after finding cocaine concealed in paintings. CBP JFK questions a smuggling suspect who doesn’t fit the typical profile. 

Suspicious Suitcase
CBP officers at MIA question a young traveler with a suspicious suitcase. HSI JFK conducts a controlled delivery of drug-filled pistons. 

Smuggle Once, Smuggle Twice
CBP agents at JFK search a traveler flying from Panama to Hong Kong with no job or money. HSI helps bust an arms trafficking ring in Buenos Aires. 

Drugs, Guns, and Money
A CBP officer at JFK finds cocaine concealed in cans of tropical fruit and HSI agents in Miami stop a date rape drug from hitting the streets.

title: To Catch a Smuggler: Drugs, Guns, and Money | S1 MEGA EPISODE | National Geographic
